title: For Sale:  Pre-Accutrigger Savage MKII BV in .22LR
postcontent:
This is a pre-accutrigger MKII BV in .22LR. It used to be called an LV for "laminated varmint," but Savage brought out left-hand rifles and switched to using the "L" designation to signify as such. As you can see, it has a salt and pepper laminate stock and heavy varmint barrel. With Wolf MT, this thing was getting between 1/2 and 3/4 MOA at 50 yards for me using a cheap Bushnell 4-12x40AO scope (which as been sold, and is NOT included in the sale!). It comes with one 5-round magazine, the owner's manual, and an old leather rifle bag. It has a dent/scratch on the muzzle that does not  interfere with the crown or affect accuracy at all.

I'm hoping to see $190 for this, but am open to reasonable offers. I'd prefer to keep this a local sale, but will ship if needed. Based on the P229®, one of the most prolific sidearms in federal law enforcement, the P224 takes the same hammer-fire reliability and lightweight all-metal frame and puts them in a subcompact package with all of the familiar SIG SAUER controls and functions.

Despite its small size, the P224 maintains a double-stack magazine for a capacity of 10 rounds of .40S&W giving the P224 a decided advantage over most subcompact

“Almost 80 percent of federal law enforcement agencies have chosen the P229 for its durability, reliability and safety,” said Ron Cohen, SIG SAUER President and Chief Executive Officer. “The P224 may be cut down in size, but it hasn’t lost an ounce of these performance features.”
